                            <comment id="14353442" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 19:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thobbs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thobbs&quot;&gt;thobbs&lt;/a&gt; What is the desired fix here? Increase the field size limit as done in the workaround? What versions should be targeted?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14353453" author="thobbs" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 19:36:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the best option is to create a cqlsh config option (just in the config file, not the command line) to specify a limit.  Let&apos;s target 2.0+.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Did you want to take this ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14353458" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 19:38:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I can get to this later today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14363436" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 16 Mar 2015 16:28:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is the 2.1 patch. Not sure if it&apos;s worth adding a new section to cqlshrc for this, but it doesn&apos;t exactly fit in ui, auth, or ssl. Also not sure if that is the best place to set the csv.field_size_limit, but it seems setting it anywhere is valid. Tested locally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14378129" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 24 Mar 2015 16:45:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think adding a new csv section is fine, because there are a few other tickets that could easily end up with a new option in that section as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1, committed as 061ea33fd.  Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
